On March 12, the China Eastern Airline announced that a team of Chinese anti epidemic experts from Italy would fly directly from Shanghai to Rome to carry out anti epidemic work, and 31 tons of medical protective materials would be randomly transported to Italy.

China has also contributed US $20 million to the World Health Organization, donated face masks, medicines, protective clothing and other epidemic prevention materials to relevant countries, and exported urgently needed medical supplies and equipment to some countries. Local governments and private institutions in China are also reaching out to other countries.

Some people worry that the domestic epidemic has not disappeared, it is too early to send experts abroad.
